src_text: Kabinete e kopane ka Laboraro, la bo 24 Motsheganong 2017, kwa Tuynhuys, Motsekapa Merero ya ga jaana Kabinete e tlhobaediwa ke ditiragalo tse di tswelelang tsa tiriso e e botlhaswa le tirisodikgoka kgatlhanong le basadi mo set habeng sa ron Ditiragalo tsa se weng tse di amang tirisodikgoka ka bakapelo di bakile gore basadi ba digatlhamelamasisi e bile ba le sebete ba bue kgatlhanong le go gatakwa ga ditshwanelo tsa bon Kabinete e amogela gore jaaka naga re tswelela go nna le set haba se se laolwang ke banna mme ka jalo e ikuela gore go dirwe go le gontsi go lwantsha tirisodikgoka kgatlhanong le basadi le kgwebisano ka bath Kabinete e ikuela go makala otlhe a set haba go dirisana mmogo go fenya bothata jo, go ganetsa mofuta ofe fela wa tirisodikgoka kgatlhanong le basadi le bana le go dirisana le sepodisi le tsamaiso ya bosiamisi go dira gore badiri ba ditiro tse di maswe tse ba lebagane le mola Moporesitente Jacob Zuma o ikuetse gore tiriso e e botlhaswa kgatlhanong le basadi le bana e khutl Kabinete e laetse Setlhopha sa Tshireletso ya Loago, Tlhabololo ya Set haba le Baagi go tsenya tirisong lenaane la tiro le le tla thusang naga go thibela tiriso e e botlhaswa ya basadi le ban Kabinete e amogela dipoelo tsa Dipatlisiso tsa Dipalopalo le Boitekanelo tsa Aforika Borwa tsa 2016 ka

Recent incidents involving intimate partner violence have seen many brave and courageous women speaking out against this violation of their rightCabinet acknowledges that as a country we continue to have a patriarchal society and as such calls for more to be done to fight the scourge of femicide and human traffickinCabinet calls on all sectors of society to join hands in defeating this scourge, trg_text: The annual commemoration of Africa Day marks the founding of the Organisation of African Unity in 1963.As we end Africa Month, Cabinet calls on all South Africans to partner with our fellow Africans residing in South Africa and elsewhere on the continent to ensure the prosperity for our region and the rest of AfricIt is also incumbent on all who reside within our borders, South Africans and foreign nationals alike to adhere to the laws of the countr Together we must fight the scourge of human trafficking, abductions, and the abuse of women and children Congratulatory messagesCabinet congratulates the Stellenbosch University and Tygerberg Academic Hospital medical team comprising of Prof Andre van der Merwe, Dr Alexander Zuhlke, Prof Rafique Moosa, Dr Amir Zarrabi and Dr Zamira Keyse They recently performed a second penis transplant, making it the first medical centre in the world to successfully perform this procedure twic The success of this procedure in the hands of our transplant team is testimony to the high level of skill and expertise that exists in the public health sector in South AfricCabinet congratulated iSimangaliso Wetland Park for receiving the Audit Excellence Award at the South African Institute of Chartered Accountants (SAICA) Public Sector Excellence Awards earlier this mont The award was in recognition of the Park receiving clean audits over five consecutive year

src_text: Se se na le ditlamorago tse di sa itumediseng mo go ba ba tla latlhegelwang ke ditiro le mo ikonoming ya ronPuso e tswelela ka maikemisetso a yona a go tshegetsa lekala la dirori mo nageng e, le le leng botlhokwa mo ikonoming le go tlhola ditirBa dti ba tswelela go dirisana le bannaleseabe botlhe go fokotsa ditlamorago tsa s Go oketsa tlhagiso, go tlholwa ga ditiro le kgolo ya thomelontle, re sa tswa go thankgolola kgato ya borobongwe ya Leanotiro la Pholisi ya Madirelo (IPAP) go re supetsa tsel Kabinete e tlhaloganya gore Isuzu, e e ntseng e le mo semphatong le GMSA dingwaga di le dintsi mo Aforika Borwa, e tla dira ditiro tse di neng di dirwa ke GMS Kabinete e lemogile go etegela ga maemo a komelelo kwa Kapa Bophirima le Kapa Botlhab Kabinete e ikuela go baagi go tshegetsa dikganelo tsa metsi tse di tlhomilweng ke diporofense tsSetlhopha se se nang le batlhankedi go tswa kwa Lefapheng la Metsi le Kgeleloleswe, Komiti ya Boset haba ya Taolo ya Matlhotlhapelo ka tirisano le diporofense le pusoselegae, e ntse e semeletse go netefatsa gore ditharabololo tsa pakakhutshwane go ya go tsa pakagare di a itlhaganedisiwa go netefatsa tshireletso ya tlamelo ka metsi mo diporofenseng tseno mo pakatelelenKabinete e ikuela go maAforika Borwa otlhe go akaretsa mo magaeng, dikgwebo, lekala la meepo, maatla le temothuo go dirisana mmogo go dirisa metsi ka tshomarel.

Management Committee working with the provinces and local government, had been actively engaged in ensuring that short to medium-term solutions are fast-tracked to guarantee the water security of the the released Anti-Corruption Strategy discussion document, which will inform the National Anti-Corruption Strateg Cabinet invites the public to make written inputs through the Department of Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation website: wwdpmgozThe fight against corruption remains one of the main priorities for governmen Corruption and integrity failures in both the private and public sector have a detrimental effect on our country s developmen Cabinet expressed concern at the recent global cyber-attack, which has been reported as the biggest cyber-attack to datCabinet urges all South Africans to take the necessary precautions when using electronic means of communicating or transactin The use of updated antivirus software which scans the environment frequently is also recommende Cabinet is concerned about the recent developments at Esko Cabinet appreciates that the matter regarding the re-employment of Mr Brian Molefe as the Chief Executive Officer of Eskom is before courts and in Parliament, and shall therefore respect these processe The President has, however, set up an Inter-Ministerial Committee (IMC) comprising the Ministers of Public Enterprises, Energy, Finance and Justice and Correctional Service The IMC is asked to gather the facts in order to guide Cabinet on how to deal with such matters in futur The convenor is the Minister of Justice and Correctional Services, Mr Michael Masutha Cabinet decisionsCabinet approved the publication of the Reviewed Broad-Based Black Economic Empowerment Charter for the South African Mining and Minerals industry in 2017.Mineral Resources Minister Mosebenzi Zwane will provide a briefing once the charter has been gazetteCabinet endorsed the approved National Radio Frequency Plan 2017 by the Ministry of Telecommunications and Postal Service The allocation of spectrum by the World Radiocommunication Conference has a significant impact on the economic growth of South AfricThe National Radio Frequency Plan 2017 is a comprehensive source of radio frequency spectrum allocation for different radiocommunication service The revised National Radio Frequency Plan 2017 ensures South Africa is aligned with the approved International Radio Regulations that were adopted in the 2015 International Telecommunication Union conferencCabinet approved the Inland Waterways Safety Strateg The strategy, through the South African Maritime Safety Authority, sets standards and enhances procedures for permitting and licensing arrangements for boats operating on inland waterway This will ensure the safety of small vessels on South Africa s inland waterwayCabinet approved the Road Freight Strateg The strategy aims to create an integrated regulatory and operational framework, which will enable South Africa to achieve best international standards of road-freight operationThe recommendations in this strategy will enhance the efficiency of enforcement, promote road safety, improve the protection of the infrastructure, reduce environmental impacts, and create an integrated framework of quality-regulated competition within which the road freight sector can continue to serve the needs of the South src_text: Kabinete gape e tlhobaediwa ke ditiragalo tsa se weng kwa Esko Kabinete e lemoga gore ntlha ya go thapiwa gape ga ga Rre Brian Molefe jaaka Motlhankedikhuduthamagamogolo (CEO) kwa Eskom e kwa kgotlatshekelo le kwa Palamenteng, ka jalo e tla ikobela ditiragalo tseLe fa go le jalo, Moporesitente o tlhomile Komiti ya Ditona (IMC) e e nang le Tona ya Dikgwebo tsa Puso, ya Maatla, ya Matlotlo le Bosiamisi le ya Ditirelo tsa Kgopolol IMC e kopilwe go kokoanya dintlha gore di kgone go kaela Kabinete gore e ka samagana jang le merero e mo isagon Moeteledipele ke Tona ya Bosiamisi le Ditirelo tsa Kgopololo, Michael Masutha Ditshwetso tsa botlhokwa tsa kabinete Kabinete e amogetse go phasaladiwa ga Tumelano e e Tlhabolotsweng ya Matlafatso e e Anameng ya Bantsho mo Ikonoming ya intaseteri ya Meepo le Diminerale ya Aforika Borwa ka 2017.Tona ya Meepo Mosebenzi Zwane o tla tlamela ka pegelo fa tumelano e e sena go phasaladiw Kabinete e mametleletse Leano la Boset haba la Marang a Radio ka Lefapha la Mafaratlhatlha a Ditlhaeletsano le Ditirelo tsa Pos Go abiwa ga marang ke Khonferense ya Lefatshe ya Radiocommunication go na le seabe sa botlhokwa mo kgolong ya Aforika BorwLeano la Boset haba la Marang a Radio ke motswedi o o tletseng wa kabo ya marang a ditirelo tse di farologaneng tsa tlhaeletsano ka radi Leano la Boset haba la Marang a Radio le le tlhabolotsweng la 2017 le netefatsa gore Aforika Borwa o nyalana le Melawana ya Bodit haba ya Radio e e amogetsweng kwa khonferenseng ya Kopano ya Mafaratlhatlha a Ditlhaeletsano ya Bodit haba (ITU) ka 2013.

src_text: Kabinete e amogetse Togamaano ya Pabalesego ya Ditselana tsa Mets Togamaano e, ka Bothati ba Pabalesego ya Mawatle a Aforika Borwa, e tlhoma maemo le go tsweletsa mekgwatsamaiso ya go letla le go rebolela dikepe dilaesense tsa go dira mo metsing a e seng a kwa mawatlen Se se tla netefatsa pabalesego ya diketswana tse mo metsing a a seng kwa mawatleng mo Aforika Borw Kabinete e amogetse Togamaano ya Dithoto mo Tselen Togamaano e e ikaelela go tlhola letlhomeso la taolo e e momaganeng e bile e dira sentle, e e tla netefatsang gore Aforika Borwa o fitlhelela maemo a a gaisang a bodit haba a ditiro tsa tsamaiso ya dithoto ka tselDikatlenegiso mo letlhomesong le di tla netefatsa nonofo ya tiragatso, thotloetso ya pabalesego mo tseleng, fokotsa seabe mo tikologong, le go tlhola letlhomeso le le momaganeng la kgaisano e e laolwang ka boleng e mo go yona lekala la tsamaiso ya dithoto ka tsela e tla tswelelang go direla ditlhokego tsa maAforika Borwa tsa ikonom Kabinete e amogetse ditebego tse di wa tsa madi a segopotso le a a tla dirisiwang ka 2017 le 2018.Ka tirisano le Kabinete, motseletsele o mo wa o, o ne wa tlhongwa go supa setso, kgololesego le temokerasi ka fa tlase ga setlhogo:
